==Description==
'''Level 258''', the 259th level of the Backrooms, takes the form of a rocky, dead landscape, currently thought to stretch out for about 1,096,128 km<sup>2</sup>. The level consists of mountains, hills, lakes, valleys, and has various "towns" consisting of dilapidated brutalist structures. It also is bordered by steep mountains of unknown height. Any attempts to scale these mountains have proven fruitless. No discovered mineshafts lead very far into the mountains, the furthest discovered being about 0.57 km past what is considered the "border".

{{Blurimage|align=right|file=pyramiden.jpg|caption=<span style="font-size:14px">The clearest photo of Level 258 submitted to the database. Photographer CA.</span>}}

'''Level 258''' is covered in a thin, misty fog at all times, and the sky is constantly covered with thick clouds. The level has a stable temperature throughout the day at a chilly 5.1 &deg;C, dropping to -0.8 &deg;C at night. As such, it is advised to avoid this level unless properly equipped for the cold. At certain times, light rain has been recorded, albeit for brief periods. '''Level 258''' has a 16-hour day/night cycle, split evenly into 8 hours between the day/night periods. However, the night period has been reported to seem nearly twice as long as the day period, even though, upon being recorded, the night period has been proven to be indeed 8 hours long. Additionally, during the night period, people have reported to feel a strong sense of anxiousness and dread.

The terrain is dotted with various hills, mountains, lakes, and valleys. This causes the terrain to be difficult to traverse. The lakes in the level contain water that is technically safe to swim in and is devoid of many waterborne viruses, including <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Hydrolitis Plague]]</span>. However, these lakes are typically around a freezing -16 &deg;C, and can cause hypothermia within a minute. It is still advised to boil the water before drinking.

The structures in the towns scattered across '''Level 258''' are at severe levels of age and decay and are in hazardous condition. The interiors are filled with dust and mold, the floors are unstable, and parts of the buildings have collapsed. The structures in question are brutalist, soviet styled refineries, apartments, stores, depots, and others. 

Despite the state of the buildings being aged and destroyed, useful items can be found inside. Although most food and water are inedible due to mold, rot, etc., objects ranging from utensils, currency (in rubles), and clothing, to precious metals, weapons and ammo (namely mid-soviet firearms such as the AK-47 and PM), and tools. Looting these buildings is advised to be done with caution, however, due to the condition the buildings are in.

Near the towns are entrances to massive mineshaft systems that span almost the entirety of the underground of '''Level 258'''. These mines can serve as a transport system; however, this is highly discouraged as the mines are very unstable and prone to collapse, along with being difficult to navigate. Additionally, an abundance of coal has been found in the mines. Other than that, and an available exit, these mines serve little purpose.

==Entities==
No living creatures are on this level, save for grass, mold, moss, etc.

==Colonies and Outposts==
'''Level 258''' is devoid of any colonies or outposts, for unknown reasons. It is not advised to attempt to create any colonies or outposts here.

==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
* Wandering through the mineshafts in <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Level 620]]</span> may transition to '''Level 258'''
* Noclipping or sleeping in the '''khrushchevkas''' in <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Level 245]]</span> can lead <b>here</b>.
* Travelling through <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Level 620]]</span> can lead you to an exit from a mineshaft <b>here</b>.
===Exits===
* Noclipping in the mines will take you to <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Level 8]]</span>.
* Swimming in the frigid waters of the lakes will eventually take you to <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Level 202]]</span>. This is not advised, as the temperature will cause hypothermia and will almost certainly be fatal.
* Spending the night in the buildings of Level 258 may seamlessly transition to the Gigakhrushchevka in <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Level 680]]</span>.
* Noclipping into the floors of Level 258's buildings will lead one to <span style="color:#6F5747">[[Level 959|there]]</span>.
