At night, '''Level 258''' takes an eerie shift. Realistically, nothing changes. The fog is just as heavy, the sky is just as cloudy, and the silence is just as prominent. But everything feels so much more alive, when dimly lit by the cloud-covered moon. 

The level seems to invoke a sense of paranoia. Of dread. You know nothing is going to happen. But it feels like something will.

People have reported hearing things. Like distant sounds of scratching, crying, screeching, etc. It has shown to not be a symptom of declining mental health, although the anxiety and paranoia are thought to be the cause.

Marks have been found on the level. Not natural destruction or wear, but actual scratch marks, seemingly made by an entity. But there is nothing to make them, so why are they there? We don't know.

Overall, the night poses no danger. However, it is recommended to take shelter and guard oneself, as being defended and taking up arms increases safety, and can be an effective way to ease someone in a stressful situation. Also, other than the little natural light from the moon, there is almost 0 light on this level, making it easy to make mistakes and harm oneself in the dark. 

And finally, spending the night out in the open increases the paranoia effects and can lead to declining mental health. Symptoms of severe paranoia include feelings of being stalked, feelings of danger, etc.
